{
  "texts": [
    "It is crucial that continuous training programs address this gap, ensuring that teachers are not only equipped to teach with technology but also to research and contribute to academic knowledge effectively.In this context, ChatGPT, developed by OpenAI, emerges as an AI language model that uses advanced natural language processing techniques to generate responses to user queries or suggestions.",
    "This model has been trained with large amounts of text and is based on the GPT-3.5 family, considered one of the most advanced in the field of language models [17].",
    "In March 2023, GPT-4, an improved version promising rapid advancements in capabilities, was released.",
    "The application of ChatGPT in education has broad and diverse potential, including drafting articles, stories, poems, and essays [18], generating summaries, expanding texts, and debugging original computer code [19].",
    "However, its use has also generated controversy regarding its suitability for education."
  ]
}